cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the optimization of deep neural networks. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the accuracy of image classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a strategy for constructing joint spaces of weights, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of fine-grained SGD for optimization suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the norms of weights in DNNs, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
